                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4131/150a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-18T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 18, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Some time ago when the Secretary first brought up the subject referred to in
                    our instruction 1130 of February 13th the Secretary told the British Ambassador
                    that he would give him a copy of the memorandum which was being drawn up on the
                    subject. He had in mind giving him the memorandum after you had had time to take
                    it up with the Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs and the interested Cabinet
                    members. We realize there may have been a delay in the consideration of this
                    matter, but in order not to wait too long before giving the Ambassador here a
                    copy we would like to know whether you have yet furnished a copy to the Foreign
                    Office or any other Government official.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
